ZCZC GE91
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 152300 UTC
THIS PERIOD CARRIES LOWER THAN AVERAGE CONFIDENCE BUT SHOULD START WITH
A 998 LOW IN THE VICINITY OF SCOTLAND LEAVING A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE OVER
SERN UK AND MUCH OF CONTINENTAL WERN EUROPE WHILE A MAJOR 990 LOW OCCUPIES
THE MID-ATLANTIC. THE INITIAL LOW SHOULD SOON LOSE ITS IDENTITY THROUGH TUESDAY
WITH THE RIDGE AMPLIFYING TO MEET WITH A HIGH OVER ICELAND FOR A TIME. THIS
HIGH SHOULD THEN BE DISPLACED NWARDS MIDWEEK AS THE ATLANTIC LOW 979 ERODES
ITS INFLUENCE IN THE SW APPROACHES. THIS GENERAL NE-SW SPLIT SHOULD SEE OUT
THE FCST PERIOD WITH THE LOW MAKING UNCERTAIN SLOW AND ERRATIC EWARD PROGRESS
LATER IN THE WORKING WEEK. THERE IS A RISK OF GALES IN CENTRAL AND LATER
NERN N SEA AREAS MONDAY AND TUESDAY EASING BY MIDWEEK. THIS SHOULD BE REPLACED
BY AN INCR CHANCE OF STRG WINDS IN WERN ENGLISH CHANNEL AREAS FM MIDWEEK
PERHAPS ALSO THE EERN SEABOARD OF BRITAIN THURSDAY
